    <string name="tutorial_1">Welcome to Chain Reaction. In the game, you need to control the rotation of your arrows to cause chain reaction, so that the opponent\'s arrow will attack his opponent and deduct the life value, and prevent the arrows from chain reaction to attack himself. When a party\'s health returns to zero, the game ends.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_2">When you rotate your arrow, the next arrow that rotates will rotate again in the same direction until the arrow points to the chessboard or attacks one game player.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_3">The red side has just rotated its red arrow, the arrow turned against the clockwise and pointed to the arrow on its right side, the arrow on the right also rotated counterclockwise, pointing to the chessboard, and the chain reaction ended.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_4">Now it\'s your turn. Please think carefully about the chain reaction caused by the rotating arrow. Click the button below to select how to operate your arrow.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_5_1">Well done! Because of your right choice, the opponent has been deducted a little health value.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_5_2">What a pity… Because of your wrong choice, you have been deducted a little health.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_6">The tutorial uses single player mode. When creating a new game, you can also choose double mode or set the size of chessboard. Slide left to open the game menu.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_7">This is the end of the tutorial. You can try to win or create a new game.</string>
